## Build and search

Every Pendragon site includes client-side search powered by
[Pagefind](https://pagefind.app/). Hugo builds the HTML; Pagefind
indexes it afterward (no Node or npm required).

```bash
hugo --minify
pagefind --site public
```

Install Pagefind once (macOS: `brew install pagefind`, or see the
[GitHub releases](https://github.com/CloudCannon/pagefind/releases)).
Then run `hugo server` and use the search box in the header — try
searching for **getting started** or **guides**.

Until you run `pagefind`, the search box stays visible but inactive;
the site otherwise works normally.
